# Calendar Skill

Use the managed CalDAV calendar handler.

## Input Contract

User input is everything after `/{{ openclaw_calendar_command_skill_name }}`.

- `today`
- `tomorrow`
- `on <YYYY-MM-DD>`
- `week [--start <YYYY-MM-DD>]`
- `free --at <datetime> [--duration <minutes>]`
- `create --calendar <id> --title <text> --start <datetime> [--duration <minutes>] [--repeat daily|weekly|monthly] [--count N | --until YYYY-MM-DD]`
- `edit <event_id> [--title <text>] [--start <datetime>] [--duration <minutes>]`
- `delete <event_id> --confirm`

`event_id` values are emitted in event listings and create output.

Natural-language mapping:

- If the user asks for "tomorrow", run `tomorrow`.
- If the user asks for "this week"/"diese Woche", run `week`.
- If the user asks for "next week"/"n√§chste Woche", run `week --start <next Monday date>`.

